divisions. In contrast, higher rates of married people and more precipitation in 
a division were significantly associated with less YLL. We provide an evidence 
base and a transferable approach that can guide health policy and intervention 
in sub-national regions afflicted by disease burden in Kenya and other areas of 
comparable settings.

